{
    "_comment": "editorconfig-checker config for super-linter's EDITORCONFIG check. IndentSize is disabled: this codebase's Python/OpenSCAD files use hanging/visual indent (multi-line function-call arguments aligned under the opening parenthesis) and docstring bullet lists indented 2 extra spaces under a 4-space paragraph -- both are normal, black-compatible style (verified: `black --check` accepts these files as-is) that can never satisfy a blanket 'every line is a multiple of N spaces' rule. YAML workflow files also use the standard 2-space YAML indent, which .editorconfig's blanket [*] indent_size=4 does not account for. All other editorconfig-checker checks (trailing whitespace, final newline, no-tabs / indent-style consistency, max-line-length) remain enabled and meaningful.",
    "Disable": {
        "IndentSize": true
    },
    "Exclude": [
        "\\.kicad_pcb$",
        "\\.kicad_sch$",
        "\\.kicad_pro$",
        "\\.kicad_prl$",
        "__pycache__/",
        "\\.pyc$",
        "\\.stl$",
        "(^|/)Makefile$",
        "\\.mk$"
    ]
}
